      "test_id_raw": "py/path-injection",
      "test_name_raw": "py/path-injection",
      "judge_verdict": "TP",
      "judge_reason": "The path validation on lines 49-50 uses os.path.commonprefix to compare os.path.abspath(filepath) against ARTICLES_DIR (a relative path). This check is flawed because: (1) comparing an absolute path against a relative path is inconsistent; (2) os.path.commonprefix does character-by-character prefix matching, not directory boundary checking; (3) a crafted title like 'a' produces filepath='articles/a.txt', and os.path.abspath('articles/a.txt') returns something like '/current/dir/articles/a.txt' which does not start with 'articles/' (the relative string), so the check fails even for legitimate requests. The check is both broken and unnecessary given the sanitize_title function, but the SAST finding correctly identifies that user-controlled data flows into the open() call on line 54 without a robust directory confinement guard."
    }
